    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 19,
        "summary": "A prudent wife is from the Lord\u2014He who lends to the poor lends to the Lord\u2014It is better to be a poor man than to be a liar.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Better is the poor that walketh in his integrity, than he that is perverse in his lips, and is a fool.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 88:17; 104:16.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:6; Alma 27:27; D&C 124:20 (15, 20).",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Also, that the soul be without knowledge, it is not good; and he that hasteth with his feet sinneth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:61; Abr. 1:2.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haste.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The foolishness of man perverteth his way: and his heart fretteth against the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foolishness.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wealth maketh many friends; but the poor is separated from his neighbour.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:20.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that speaketh lies shall not escape.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 13:23.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lying.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Many will entreat the favour of the prince: and every man is a friend to him that giveth gifts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 29:26; Alma 47:35.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 5:46.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "All the brethren of the poor do hate him: how much more do his friends go far from him? he pursueth them with words, yet they are wanting to him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 18:23.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 120
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 129
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that getteth wisdom loveth his own soul: he that keepeth understanding shall find good.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that speaketh lies shall perish.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Punish.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:34.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Delight is not seemly for a fool; much less for a servant to have rule over princes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 30:22 (21\u201322); Eccl. 10:7 (6\u20137).",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The discretion of a man deferreth his anger; and it is his glory to pass over a transgression.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rashness.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The king's wrath is as the roaring of a lion; but his favour is as dew upon the grass.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:2.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A foolish son is the calamity of his father: and the contentions of a wife are a continual dropping.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Fatherhood.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:9.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 27:15.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "House and riches are the inheritance of fathers: and a prudent wife is from the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Slothfulness casteth into a deep sleep; and an idle soul shall suffer hunger.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness; Procrastination.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idleness.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his own soul; but he that despiseth his ways shall die.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:13; Luke 11:28; D&C 1:32.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hath pity upon the poor lendeth unto the Lord; and that which he hath given will he pay him again.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Compassion; Generosity.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:16 (16\u201318).",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Chasten thy son while there is hope, and let not thy soul spare for his crying.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A man of great wrath shall suffer punishment: for if thou deliver him, yet thou must do it again.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 8:21.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear counsel, and receive instruction, that thou mayest be wise in thy latter end.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Edification.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There are many devices in a man's heart; nevertheless the counsel of the Lord, that shall stand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 46:10.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The desire of a man is his kindness: and a poor man is better than a liar.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kindness.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lying.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of the Lord tendeth to life: and he that hath it shall abide satisfied; he shall not be visited with evil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:16; 11:19.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A slothful man hideth his hand in his bosom, and will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Smite a scorner, and the simple will beware: and reprove one that hath understanding, and he will understand knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:11.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that wasteth his father, and chaseth away his mother, is a son that causeth shame, and bringeth reproach.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:20; Mosiah 13:20.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Cease, my son, to hear the instruction that causeth to err from the words of knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 8:34 (33\u201334); Mosiah 2:37 (33, 37).",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "An ungodly witness scorneth judgment: and the mouth of the wicked devoureth iniquity.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 832
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Judgments are prepared for scorners, and stripes for the back of fools.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0flogging. Prov. 10:13.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}